WEBVTT

00:00.301 --> 00:01.251
Charlie: <i>Previously on "Manhattan"... </i>

00:01.302 --> 00:03.253
Because on July 4th, 1945,

00:03.988 --> 00:06.907
we're going to test the
gadget in our own backyard.

00:06.908 --> 00:09.910
Frank: <i>The Army manipulated
us, you and I, Charlie.</i>

00:10.361 --> 00:11.693
<i>We have to stop this train.</i>

00:11.729 --> 00:13.196
He doesn't just want a seat at the table.

00:13.230 --> 00:15.815
He wants to shut down the project.

00:15.866 --> 00:18.568
If you thought you were racing
the Nazis to a super weapon,

00:18.619 --> 00:20.820
<i>your ignorance has been engineered.</i>

00:20.871 --> 00:22.906
I gave up my one shot at history

00:22.957 --> 00:24.457
so you could get us a seat at the table.

00:24.491 --> 00:28.077
You excited to incinerate 20,000 kids?

00:28.128 --> 00:31.130
I think Frank Winter sabotaged the pretest.

00:31.165 --> 00:33.833
This test is the start of a whole new era,

00:33.884 --> 00:37.720
like Auro's interplanetary cruise
ship crash-landing on Jupiter.

00:37.755 --> 00:40.556
- Are you a spy, Jim?
- Uh, Jeannie, wait!

00:40.591 --> 00:42.225
Jim! I'll handle this.

00:43.894 --> 00:45.728
I'm not going to Trinity.

00:45.763 --> 00:47.146
I'm grateful for the opportunities

00:47.181 --> 00:48.731
you've given me here, Charlie,

00:48.766 --> 00:51.901
but I've had enough death for one lifetime.

00:51.936 --> 00:54.687
- Where's Joey?
- He's on his way to Brooklyn.

00:54.738 --> 00:58.441
<i>Juanita's driving him. He's
going to live with my parents.</i>

00:58.492 --> 01:00.193
Keeping him safe from you,

01:00.244 --> 01:01.861
just like you should have been
kept safe from your father!

01:01.912 --> 01:03.863
You think I won't get in
the car and bring him back?

01:03.914 --> 01:06.582
Your test is in 24 hours.

01:06.617 --> 01:08.584
You think I don't know
which way you'll drive?

01:08.619 --> 01:12.372
You, a guy who went to
a second-rate law school,

01:12.423 --> 01:16.042
is getting orchestra
seats to physics history?

01:16.093 --> 01:17.760
Nora: <i>You and Perseus</i>

01:17.795 --> 01:19.379
<i>are going to go out there on your own.</i>

01:19.430 --> 01:21.180
You built the circuits.

01:21.215 --> 01:23.716
You can wire them to go
off at any time you like.

01:23.767 --> 01:27.136
Meeks: <i>You want to kill the scientists.</i>

01:27.187 --> 01:29.973
<i>You want to kill my friends.</i>

01:30.024 --> 01:32.442
Paul?

01:32.476 --> 01:34.227
We need to talk about Jim.

01:41.285 --> 01:42.785
Stan: Last car leaves the blast zone

01:42.820 --> 01:45.405
at zero minus 30 minutes.

01:45.456 --> 01:47.156
They test the firing switch...

01:47.207 --> 01:50.543
Meeks: Two hours earlier. I know.

01:50.577 --> 01:52.412
Stan: So you rig the detonator

01:52.463 --> 01:54.213
to go off when Isaacs hits the switch.

01:54.248 --> 01:57.417
The bomb fizzles and scatters plutonium

01:57.468 --> 01:59.802
<i>halfway to El Paso.</i>

01:59.837 --> 02:01.971
Killing all the staff on the ground.

02:04.475 --> 02:07.810
I think we should stick
to the original plan.

02:07.845 --> 02:10.229
Hold off till everyone evacuates.

02:10.264 --> 02:12.815
Just... just you and me now, right?

02:12.850 --> 02:15.818
The decision is ours.

02:15.853 --> 02:19.022
We're not the directors of this play.

02:19.073 --> 02:22.575
- We're the actors.
- What's your part?

02:22.609 --> 02:24.444
Make sure I do mine?

02:29.416 --> 02:30.917
Frank: <i>But where's the proof, Paul,</i>

02:30.951 --> 02:33.252
besides some baseball hat?

02:33.287 --> 02:35.588
Meeks was the most
devoted member of my group.

02:35.622 --> 02:37.256
I practically had to
crowbar him out the door

02:37.291 --> 02:39.509
to attend his own mother's funeral.

02:41.595 --> 02:43.296
What?

02:51.021 --> 02:52.688
(Sighs)

